This will guide you through the preparaion of the enveronment to run the code

## REQUIREMENTS
Python version 3.0 to above
To check your current version: python --version
To update python: winget upgrade --id Python.Python.3 (Open CMD as administrater if required) (For windows)
To install freshly, download the latest version from: www.python.org/downloads/

## Step 1: Install dependencies
Run the code: pip install rdkit pandas

## Step 2: Preparition of directory
1. Clone this repository in your system
2. Enter to the directory named "Lipinski_Calculator"
-------------------------or-------------------------
1. create a directory with any name as per your convenience
2. Save "Lipinski.py" in that directory

3. Save your smiles.smi file in the same directory (Example smiles.smi file given)

------------------------------WINDOWS AND WSL-------------------------
## Step 3: Run the program:
1. Open terminal in the directory
2. Run the code: python calculate_lipinski.py smiles.smi lipinski_results.csv

NOTE: lipinski_results.csv will be saved in the same directory







